#Text=Egypt struggles to recover tourism , investment
#Text=Friday , February 10 , 2012
#Text=The Egyptian pound is currently falling in value .
#Text=Image : Mabuhelwa .
#Text=Standard & Poor 's downgraded Egypt 's currency rating for the second time in four months based on the country 's shorfall in foreign reserves and shaky political transition .
#Text=It 's the latest development for a nation facing mounting economic diffuclties .
#Text=Egypt 's foreign reserves fell by over 50 percent last year to about US$ 16 billion .
#Text=Egypt has requested US$ 3.2 billion from the International Monetary Fund to bolster its reserves and prevent a devalation but that could take months .

#Text=Experts say that Egypt 's problem of attracting foreign investment and tourists , which are two sources that would increase reserves , has already caused the Egyptian pound to lose 1 percent of its value and if the country does n't solve the shortfall in foriegn currency , it could even lead to a further currency devaluation within the next two to three months .
#Text=The long-term solution is to restore tourism and foreign investments but both are suffering because of the continuing unrest .
#Text=Tourism
#Text=The Sphynx was said to guard the city of Thebes by killing anyone who could n't answer a riddle .
#Text=Image : Schreibkraft .
#Text=Egyptian tourism suffered this past year as a result of a revolution , a transition to an elected government , and continuing signs of unrest and instability .
#Text=The Egyptian Revolution began on January 25 last year and President Hosni Mubarak resigned over two weeks later on February 11 .
#Text=The protests have continued as Egyptians grew uncomfortable with the military 's control over the transition .
#Text=At the start of this month , 79 people were killed at a soccer event in Port Said .
#Text=Tourism in Egypt accounted for US$ 12.5 billion in 2010 but fell 30 percent , or US$ 8.8 billion , in 2011 , according to Mounir Fakhry Abdel Nour , Egypt 's tourism minister .
#Text=Tourism accounts for 11.6 percent of Egypt 's GDP .
#Text=Tourists visit The Valley of the Kings in Egypt .
#Text=It holds 63 tombs and chambers for Pharaohs and nobles of the New Kingdom era .
#Text=The valley is on the west bank of the Nile across from Thebes .
#Text=Image : Markh .
#Text=Last week , two U.S. female tourists and their Egyptian guide were abducted in the Sinai peninsula by Bedouin tribesmen and released shortly afterward .
#Text=The kidnapping took place in broad daylight on a busy road while the tourists travelled after a visit to St. Catherine 's Monastery .
#Text=Masked tribesmen stopped their bus , abducted the tourists by gunpoint , and escaped into the mountains .
#Text=Three other tourists of unknown nationalities were left on the bus .
#Text=Local authorities organized a search which ended in negotiations with local Bedouin tribesmen .
#Text=The Bedouin demanded the release of recently apprehended tribesmen , who had been detained for drug trafficking and robbery .
#Text=The US hostages were released unharmed , Abdel Nour said .
#Text=As a location , Egypt boasts ancient pyramids , the Nile River , Biblical sites like Mount Sinai , museums , and Red Sea coastal resorts .
#Text=Last year the number of tourists plunged from fifteen million people down to nine million , which is a 40 percent drop .
#Text=A camel resting between rides at the Pyramids in Egypt .
#Text=Image : Crashsystems .
#Text=The low amount of tourism to Egypt has also affected tourism in other countries .
#Text=Stas Misezhnikov , Israeli tourism minister , said that Israeli tourism is down because the flow of tourism from Egypt 's Sharm el-Sheikh resort is " almost nonexistent right now .
